reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee, delicious breakfast sandwiches! Try the market bagel.  The staff is friendly and aren't in a rush even with a line behind you. The service is very intentional and the place was clean. 4 stars for atmosphere because it was louder than I expected it to be and more kids, dogs, and family. But I liked the overall vibe.

reviews_data.review_text: One of The best places to eat meat and socialize do business.
Waffle was cold. eggs and  hash browns barely warm.

The Peoples Market in Elizabeth, Charlotte, NC offers some truly tasty breakfast options—my bagel was great and the grits were absolutely amazing, rich and flavorful. The coffee was solid as well, a nice complement to the meal. The atmosphere is cozy and inviting, making it a pleasant spot to start the day. My only downside was the order and pickup system, which felt a bit cumbersome and took away from the overall experience. Despite that, the quality of the food and drinks definitely makes it worth a visit!

Such a chill relaxing fun spot ✌️. The food and cappuccino were delicious! I had the salmon sandwich, and it was absolutely delish. Everyone who works there is so sweet and welcoming. I also really love the concept of the place, it’s unique and well thought out.

Thank you The People's Market Elizabeth:)

Emily with Offline - Every time we come here we get something even more delicious than the last. The vegan "chicken" sandwich is so good as is the actual chicken sandwich. The cocktails are always good and reasonably priced. Serving sizes are massive especially for the fries!

The People’s Market is a cool little spot that is perfect for Jen and I, as they have pizza and beer for me, and coffee and other options for Jen (she got the Pesto with Orzo Salad and loved it). They also have some good looking desserts. We got the Oreo brownie and it was pretty good, but will try something else next time.

The pizza was good and the ingredients were tasty, but it was one of the worst made pizzas I’ve had in awhile, as there were two large air bubbles on it, so some areas with no cheese…

They also had a THC infused pizza for $23.99, which I have never seen before… At first I just saw a frozen pizza for $23.99 and couldn’t believe it was so expensive, until I realized what it was.
Usually a really good spot to work but the air is ALWAYS broken!

We need this kind of option in Ballantyne! How quaint! Coffee, tea, and pastries at one counter. Draft beer in the center. Prepared food in the fridge! Huge organic drink selection. Warm sandwiches, cold sandwiches, and a large variety of chips...and seating galore! I love this atmosphere. I plan to go back! Soon!

Only my second visit, and the flow has changed.  It was difficult to tell where to order food, by the deli windo or at the coffee/tea counter... so after walking to both we went to bar in the middle. Since we were going to have a beer, bar tender said we could sit there and he would also take the order for food.  We still had to go to the deli window to pick up the food.  So a little bit of code to decipher, didnt see any signage that helped....
It wasn't crowded when we arrived, but if got more crowded while there.   It's a hard space, so noise was a factor.
Ok, food was great.  3 of us had a sandwich, a salad and a pizza.  We got Pizza as we saw a table that had one and it looked good....  it was REALLY  good.  Salad and sandwich were also excellent.
We will visit again..., hopefully we can figure out where to order what....

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped in for a quick bite. Ordered and was told I would get a text when my meal was ready. 25 minutes later and nothing. Food had been sitting for who knows how long. Fries were soggy and burger wrapper was completely torn up. They remade it but when I went to taste my fries on the way home they were covered in sugar. The AC was broken and it was about 99 degrees in there. Very disappointed.
The food was delicious.  I had a burger for dinner and ate my salad the next day.
Whomever decided to put corn chips in the breakfast burrito deserves everything good.

I want to love this place. The vibe is great, the food and drinks hit the spot, and it’s one of my favorite atmospheres in Charlotte. But the service—especially at the bar—is consistently disappointing.

Every time I visit, there are multiple staff standing around while bar customers get ignored. It’s not a one-off issue; it happens often with me waiting at the bar.

I keep coming back because of the potential this spot has, but the experience rarely matches the energy the place gives off. Hoping the service catches up to the rest of what makes People’s Market special.  I'd spend more but there is no service at the bar...

reviews_data.review_text: Check your receipt! The specials on the sign next to the register rang up higher than the sign said they are. When I noticed after paying and asked the cashier to adjust it, she said she could not because of how the POS was set up. It’s a yummy spot that I used to frequent a lot but that  left a bad taste in my mouth.

LOVED the selection of vegan food, especially the decadent donuts! My only issue was not in anyone's control. The ac was out, during a time of record breaking summer heat. It happens, so I don't hold it against the restaurant. They accommodated everyone well with as many fans as possible, and the staff was still working to uphold some great standards. Props to them!

Good vibe, I like that there is an open window. Coffee quality could be better.

2025 edit. I feel like a lot of cafes have lowered the quality of their drinks. this place retains its quality.
Great Atmosphere welcoming vibe. Food looks great definitely will have to try food items next
Service was amazing!
Perfect service, clean setting, and flavorful food.
Great spot to grab a sandwich or coffee
Seriously, the best food! If you like lox and bagels get the smoked salmon breakfast sandwich! Chef’s kiss!

I guess the only way to reach this place is to leave a one star review. I’ve tried calling, messaging on IG and the contact tab on your website and still no response. On last Friday I paid for two orders of kids chicken tenders between 3:00-3:30 via an online order. The chicken tenders were not edible and basically burnt. All I want is my money back for the meal that I paid for. If someone could actually respond to a customer’s request that would be nice.

This is the second time in 4 months I’ve been double charged for coffee / matcha. My fault for not realizing sooner, but upon checking my card after I left I was charged $12.61 for ONE iced matcha. This happened months ago as well but was never given a receipt because the barista never spun the IPad around. Whether she took it upon herself to give herself a tip or double charge, this is absurd to occur twice. No receipt to prove it of course, but done going back there. Baristas already with an attitude and then they can’t do their job properly. Judging by other reviews I’m not the only one with this experience.
Pricey
If didn't live do far away, I'd eat there daily.
Great place to eat this is definitely a hidden gem in Charlotte! & The Salty Mango is NEXT LEVEL. ✨
Visited around 10:15am on a Thursday. Not too crowded. Breakfast burrito with GF wrap was delicious and so was my cold brew. The employees are nice and the atmosphere is welcoming.
Lots of homeless folks gathered around entrance…
I love this place. Staff is great and the food is good.
Food is delicious...

The avocado chicken wrap was delicious. The burger was really good too.  Love the bacon and flavors on it. The Cinnabon is top notch. Absolutely delicious.  I got one and shared with my husband when I got home and we both wish I had got 2. Highly recommend.  It is on the loud side if you are trying to catch up with a friend.

I’ve ordered from here a couple times, but my most recent experience really prompted the 2 star review. Overall their food is pretty basic. I have previously ordered the hot honey salmon and veggies before and found a produce sticker still on the bell pepper, and the salmon was cold. Not the best presentation, but it wasn’t inedible. Nevertheless, I still ordered from here again because it’s quick and decently priced. I saw on their Instagram that the special was salmon tacos and they looked so good (I’m begging everyone to go look at the pics and then look at the photo below). Again it is fast service but when I opened my container I noticed that they slapped two shells down and then just tossed everything else on top. Salmon and sauce were cold and I had to reassemble the tacos to even attempt to eat them. To add insult to injury, the shells ripped open before I could take a bite because they were very soggy from the wet sauce. I may give this place another shot when they open their second location on selwyn but I think I’m done with the elizabeth location.
Amazing food loved the chicken and everyone at my job loves the pizza.. ❤️❤️❤️

I would not consider this an allergy-friendly restaurant. Quite frankly, if a kitchen and restaurant do not care about the health of their customers, what are they even doing cooking food for other people?

I ordered the chicken avocado wrap with a gluten-free tortilla (which I paid extra for) and asked for no cheese. I also ordered a grilled cheese with fries and ketchup. I was a little taken aback when I realized my wrap wasn’t labeled gluten-free, but I tried to keep an open mind. Then I noticed it had cheese in it as well.

I called the restaurant to confirm whether it was a gluten-free wrap. The person on the phone just tried to describe it to me, but honestly, there was no way to tell. I was left with food that I couldn’t be sure was safe for me to eat.

The grilled cheese we ordered was burned, but I didn’t even bother bringing it up because it was already clear they had no process for handling issues with orders and didn’t consider it important enough to escalate to a manager. I did mention that they forgot the ketchup; however, the woman on the phone decided to blame the Grubhub driver for that.

Explain to me how it’s the driver’s job to pick up ketchup, napkins, and silverware. They work for Grubhub—they’re a delivery driver. Why should they be doing the restaurant’s job? Plus, the bag was stapled shut when it arrived. Was he supposed to bring those items in his pockets?

Disappointing and not like I remember it when it was the Dilworth location.

Really disappointed in how highly reviewed this place is because it does not deserve it and I had a terrible breakfast because of it. Firstly I’m not sure why they don’t have a single basic smoothie on the menu, but I decided to order the one with cinnamon because I thought between that and chia seeds, it would be a less intense addition to the smoothie. It was not, there was so much cinnamon and protein powder that it was unbearable to drink. Secondly, I would like to know why restaurants don’t seem to be seasoning their food anymore. The barbacoa breakfast tacos I received were nearly inedible. There was way too much meat, they barely put any cheese or egg on it and it tasted like they didn’t even salt the meat. The prices are decent but that’s about the only good thing I have to say about my meal.
So appreciate people's market providing a comfortable and convenient community meeting place. Great example of a business providing a wonderful and much needed community service!
The best cinnamon roll of my 29 years of life
Wide variety of food and adult beverages.
Excellent food and drinks. Customer service was great.

Awkward first visit. Staff reacted as if we knew the mojo. All orders taken up front, but food menu posted in the back. More comfortable seating is warranted. The coffee and the egg sandwich were good. The text notifying us the order was ready came through @ 9:18 am. We checked on our order @ 9:06 am ... it was already sitting on the counter.

Found this place from co-worker. Love the calming and welcoming atmosphere for all ages and social levels! Just covered the love of Lattes! I am not a coffee fan and main stream coffee shops have a bitter coffee taste in lattes, so I am very particular about how it’s made. Our server was patient and able to make the latte to me liking!  Only request, don’t get me jokes on an item and it disappears!! My first visit has triple berry biscuit (scone). Some returning from London, wanted a true English scone it the biscuit was it!!! Unfortunately, during my second visits it was no longer available! Please bring it back. 😊
Love the service they give it’s nice and neat and clean good music it’s like a little vibe in there love it

reviews_data.review_text: Most of the menu that I have tried is really good except on of the breakfasts which was the Belgium waffel and hashbrowns which came with only 1/2 the waffle! We are talking batter not some high end food item and they give you 1/2 of the waffle??! Then they through in some sort of 2/3rds of a hotdog?? For 14.00 bucks meanwhile my friend got almost twice the food for 13.00 bucks on some other breakfast selection. Big issue I have is their ordering system it’s a total circus you go to the far back of the restaurant and look at the menu screen then pick what you want the walk all the way up to the front to order your food and try to remember what you picked out and what they call the item you picked out. Then they take your phone “data snatching to have your phone inundated with spam phone calls and texts” to let you know your order is up. Which also was a pain and totally a mess. My friends phone was texts to let him know his food was ready and I got all the way back to the building to get it for him and low and behold his food was not ready but my was even though I was not texted to let me know my food was ready so I wait about another 5 min to see if my friends food is ready and nothing so I go back to the front were you eat and wait and wait and nothing and there is not a single person in the back we’re you can ask “Were is my food!” I had to walk back of the building constantly to see if my friends food was ready it was a complete joke how this system of ordering and picking up your food! And no one there to ask if your food was ready. I almost gave up thinking someone walked away with my friends food. People the whole time were just walking up and taking food anyone could just take your ordered food and walk off and there is no one to stop them or check to make sure it goes to the correct person. Total 🤡🤡🤡 the one thing that was really good though is their pizza
Tad expensive but worth it
Great Macha green tea
Cute, bustling food hall with fun atmosphere but not a ton of choices for food. We had pizza which was amazing! Had ice cream for dessert, also delicious!
The burgers are PHENOMENAL ! I've been waiting to order from here for weeks.. A girlfriend of mines raves about it, and now I finally understand ! I will definitely be ordering again !
Great place for a lot of good things

Cool spot. Been here three times. Can’t say I’ll be back. The food is pretty mid for the price you pay. Not crazy expensive, but certainly not worth it. Portion sizes are on the smaller side as well.

Where they really fall short though is the service. It’s ridiculously slow. When they’re not busy it still takes forever to get your food, regardless if you put an order in ahead of time or not. And if they are busy, forget about it. Super disorganized and they seemingly prioritize Uber eats and those sorts of orders over people who were already there or people who are waiting to pick up their online order. Having to wait 45+ minutes for a simple breakfast sandwich or some rice and chicken or a pizza, that I already ordered, is not fun. This isn’t just my experience. I’ve seen people wait and complain about long wait times every time I’ve been here. It’s a regular thing for them.

1st time here. Large space. Different areas to sit.

Large menu.
Lunch (panini, SP fries, & iced coffee) cost me $26 before tip. Food was good.
Crowded but I found a place to sit.
I received salmonella food poisoning from this restaurant on 3/26/2025
A must try. Amazing eatery. Excellent food.
If you like raw chicken, you’re gonna love this place!

Wild. Half a dozen people working and I just left after 15 minutes when no one would take my order. Almost understandable when 90% of the people there are staring into laptops not ordering anything but still not ok.
The Cobb salad with the honey Siracha bacon was phenomenal also the pesto dressing and the ranch which are both made in house!! I’ll be back thank you!

This was my first time trying The People’s Market, and unfortunately, it was also my last. I ordered the chicken sandwich and ended up with food poisoning. Even though the place is cute, I’d never come back after that experience!

The peoples market display’s an unfortunate amount of negligence for their customers. After clearly outlining a gluten allergy for my girlfriend (she’s celiac) they assured us everything would be good to go. Clearly since i’m writing this review, it was not. They used a normal wrap despite clearly being told not to, as indicated on the receipt. She’s now incredibly sick and we may need to go to the hospital. They also overcharged us nearly $10 for our food, giving the prices on their menu were correct. Never again.
Great local spot to grab a coffee and simple, yet yummy breakfast.

reviews_data.review_text:
Impossible burger was good 7/10.
Italian sausage Pizza was great 8/10, would go back for this.
Coffee was 3/10 not for avid coffee drinker, she tried to remade the coffee but was still bad. I’ll try the tea next time.
No table service You serve yourself.
fresh food with good variety, chill spot for kids and groups of any age,

Incredibly delicious gluten-free, vegan treats! It's so hard to find baked goods that are both. Also, the price was so affordable. I got 2 donuts, a muffin, and a piece of blueberry lemon loaf for just $15.

Quiera with Offline - the vibe is always top tier at the People’s Market! the staff are chill and helpful, drinks amazing and don’t get me started on the amazing eats.. if it’s your first time try any BLT you won’t regret it!

This was my first time at People’s Market. The place was packed at 1 pm on a Saturday.  Many folks were on their laptops while meeting with others. We ordered two hot chocolates, a breakfast bowl, and a waffle with fruit on top.  The food took a long time so my husband  went to inquire.  We first received two cups of cold chocolates followed by our entrees which were also cold. We were unsure as to how long they had been sitting at the counter. We sat nearby but no one called out our name or brought our food to the table which was nearby.  The food was ok at best. We wanted to love this place but we unfortunately did not have a great experience.

Home of the incredible disappearing burrito! I get it- there is an egg shortage and prices are skyrocketing but the shrinkflation at this place is crazy. The breakfast burrito was smaller than the palm of my hand and it obvious they are rationing their eggs. Just charge the price you need to charge to actual have consistency. The portions are half the size they were just last month. I unwrapped the burrito and it looked like they put half an egg in it. Weve order take out and dine in there recently and both were tiny. I don’t even like big portions but this is ridiculous!
Love this place.  Everything I order is sooo good.
First visit and will not be my last! I enjoyed the atmosphere, friendly service and fast food service! It was a busy day and as soon as I sat down my order was ready!
They are a bit pricey, but the vegan chicken sandwich I had was tasty.

Oof, this place was mentioned to me by a person working at the hospital when i went to visit someone. TLDR: i wont be back… can’t recommend.

I like knowing where i stand with people, and people’s market let me know i cant stand with them. So its easy to not go back.

Id rather starve a few hours or walk over to hawthornes, menya, or even 7th street deli.

Ordered coffees, a pizza, and fries, and a sandwich ( i try to block out bad experiences and this was 2 months ago, so its a bit tough to remember the specific order, but it was the experience that mostly didn’t do it for me).

The food was alright (pizza was very meh, and i dont know how you can mess up fries, but there i was throwing money in the trash cuz i didn’t finish those cold pieces of potatoes)… but the person at the register could only have been less helpful if she had just walked away and let me do everything. So there i was struggling to make it work holding my order.
No offers of a straw, a carrying thing for coffees, a bag… i had to ask for each thing and handle it myself… it wasn’t busy, not like they couldn’t have done just a little more…
This is why i hate to tip when i order (regretfully i did and just chalk it up to a lesson learned by not revisiting), because you never know what kind of service or food you will get until after…

We stopped in for a sandwich and snack.  We ordered a club  sandwich, danish, and a few cups of tea.  The sandwich was packed full of meats.  I would have preferred it a little more toasted, but it tasted great.  The tea and danish were excellent. Out the door for just under $30.  We would eat here again.

I had the pleasure of visiting The People’s Market for the first time recently, and I couldn’t have been more impressed. Maleeka (spelling?) provided outstanding service from start to finish. She took the time to thoroughly explain the menu and all available options, which was incredibly helpful for a first-time visitor like me. Her friendly demeanor and genuine enthusiasm made the experience all the more enjoyable.

The highlight was the mocha latte she prepared—hands down one of the best I’ve ever had! The balance of flavors was perfect, and the care she put into making it was evident in every sip.

Thanks to Maleeka’s exceptional hospitality and skill, I am already looking forward to my next visit to The People’s Market. Highly recommend stopping by for excellent service and amazing coffee!
Lovely brunch and delicious coffee

I wanted pizza and gave the fig and pig a try. The toppings were generous and properly distributed . The crust was perfectly crispy yet chewy and flavorful. I was going to save the second half for later but devoured it in one fell swoop. Delicious!
As always, the vibes are amazing and the food is delicious
Always a great experience here!

Ordered their “popular” market bagel. If you are going to make egg selection an option, they need to 1. Learn how to cook a medium egg and 2. Don't serve undercooked eggs. with basically raw egg white. You threw a quarter of an avocado on the sandwich, not even sliced. Listen if you’re tired of making breakfast just stop because you destroyed mine. The other sides and my partners breakfast is “mid” at best. Thanks for wasting my money on your garbage breakfast. I would just close up if you cannot even make an egg to an order.

Really enjoyed dinner at The People's Market. My wife and I thought the smashburger was awesome. It doesnt look imposing, but it tasted amazing! The mushroom pizza was pretty good. I prefer it cooked a little more, but it was still delicious. My wife's salad was solid as well. After a beer at the bar, we finished with the malted iced coffee which was a perfect closer! Service was quick and the staff was friendly. We'll definitely be back.
Burnt!!! I believe in first impressions…..
Excellent service specifically the coffee shop!
Excellent service and breakfast was amazing. Atmosphere is always welcoming 🌞

I was driving around and stumbled upon this place. I love the whole concept of this restaurant! the atmosphere, the service and especially the food. I had a gingerbread chai latte which was very much delicious and their fried chicken sandwich definitely will be back!

Food and coffee was so good. Love the vibe. Wish the WiFi worked though. I came to do homework and was unable to get connected so I  had to leave. Once that issue is resolved, this place will be 10/10!

I came to grab a grubhub order and I planned to order for myself as well; this was at 2:00pm on 1/7/25. I never made an order because of how unwelcoming and unpleasant the cashier was being all because I asked where to pick up the online orders. She gave me attitude and pointed to the back of the store with a menacing look on her face...there are no signs in the front of the store indicating to driver's to go to the back of the store to pick up orders. With that, I didn't want to invite that horrible energy into my life again so I didn't make my order and I canceled the grubhub pick up SMH l. I thought I found my next spot to get tea, guess not.

I meant to write this sooner but the tall brown skinned gentleman (Jameel I believe), his customer service was awesome. It was my first time and he was professional, funny, and made the Lavendar iced matcha great! I also tried the sweet potatoe pecan loaf WOW! It was the perfect size as well, not too small or big.
Anyway again great service and even though I took the items to go, the inside was very big.
Picked up my food, and employee told me that my name is weird. Really classy!

This place is relaxed, service is good and people are friendly/pretty chill.

Everyday food with a little flair and creativity, locally owned, and more Vegan/Vegetarian options and substitutions than more places. Very accommodating since my last visit.

Vegan Philly (V) - Overall, it's good. It's just impossible beef with condiments - exactly as described, which I appreciate. It does need a little more "pizzazz" like seasoning (herbs & spices are vegan - idk why restaurants are afraid to use them) , lettuce, tomatoes... Etc. However, I must admit that I prefer it slightly more than the Beyond Steak. Nevertheless, my previous comment still stands and I highly recommend they make this more like a "chopped cheese" since its Impossible Burger with the chunks not being so big  but can still call it a Philly since it's just chopped meat anyway.

Vegan Fried Chicken (V) - It's GOOD AND SEASONED (I need to know their secrets lol) and the flavors work well together. The only problem is the oyster mushroom stem. They fry the entire thing but the stem is too rough and inedible. I wish they would cut it off. I've cooked these mushrooms before and you can cut most of it off leaving the rest intact.

I really do like this place, and they do a good job but I think some minor adjustments could make certain menu items much better.
Just another "market" where you herd in and herd out....nothing special.
It truly is a great hangout spot. Definitely worth recommending for a casual get together.
Very expensive mid food.

It had been a while since my last visit to people's market.  Went there the other day, and the vibe inside is VERY nice.

The staff were informative and helpful.   They seemed welcoming and especially accommodating when dealing with my 4 year old son.  Who, at the time, was intent on dismantling their Christmas tree.

The selection of baked goods was phenomenal.  My lil guy was thrilled with the Chocolate donut, covered in icing and sprinkles.

I went back a couple of days later and had a smashburger from the grill. It was delicious.

I will admit, the sandwich did not come as ordered... (keep in mind my toddler was staging considerable distractions) I asked for a "Bacon BBQ burger"without pickled onions, and ended up with a "People's smash burger" which had a hefty load of pickles on it...

Even with that easily understandable error, the burger was pretty great.  I have to imagine the other sandwich would've been even more enjoyable.

We'll be back soon

reviews_data.review_text: Nice vibe to sit down and grab a bite to eat.
Wonder surroundings with a good mix of food and drink offerings. The meeting room is it over the top.

Ordered from here 3 times through Ubereats. The grits are amazing but any other food I get always has something wrong with it. The waffle was half-raw and the fruits are always close to rotting (not fresh at all).
We go every time my wife has to go in for treatments. She especially loves the pastries.

Fried chicken was great, and the gravy was super tasty! Grits were very good. Sausage was very smokey, so mame sure that is your thing. Everything was good, but is all served in a to-go container. Coffee and smoothie bars are cool, but coffee bar was out of all seasonal syrups advertised on the door and bar. And smoothies are a bit pricey at $10-15/each.

I ordered a pickup order and they forgot my hashbrowns for my kid's burrito side as well as the honey mustard sauce for my kid's chicken tender. They can't even get an order correct... I tried to call them and no answer..... The oreo brownie was incredibly dry and old.... Horrible. Never returning

I’ve been to many spots to try a good chocolate croissant and I can say this spot has the best one 🔥 it’s Sooooo good. This spot it’s a vibe too!

Update- 12/7 second time coming and the WiFi is not working. That sucks for me because I plan to get work done and I end up having to go elsewhere. Please get this fixed!!!
Best burger in Charlotte.

I got the vegan breakfast burrito (with the vegan sausage but without the vegan cheese) plus an oat milk mocha and an oreo brownie. Everything was so yummy. The spicy green sauce that comes with the burrito is awesome. Very spicy.

reviews_data.review_text: Have gotten several things ordered through DoorDash and everything has been fresh and delicious. Food is much more seasoned compared to the other markets in the area which is a welcome change. Would recommend this place for sure.

I would have called and taken this up with the store personally but they do not have a phone number and do not allow calls so unfortunately my only way to make them aware of the serious food hazard I just experienced when trying to eat my food I ordered from them via Door Dash is to make this review and post it so that as many people as possible will know and can keep themselves safe.

A large piece of thread was in sandwich and began choking me when I took my first bite.
This could have been disastrous.

Again, I wish I had a way to let the kitchen know so that they can be aware and no one else gets hurt but this is my only option.

Please see picture below.

Thank you, Leigh.
I had the black bean burger and it was very delicious!
Thanksgiving meal def hit the spot.

Went in for something quick to hold me over until a late afternoon lunch. Shared a Peoples Smashburger and a bag of chips with my mom - we loved it. I really enjoyed the atmosphere as well. It seems like a good spot to work and catch up with friends. And they have a bit of everything including infused drinks in the cooler 😉.

I love this place, but the wifi is really inconsistent. For somewhere with a dedicated conference room and lots of folks clearly working on their laptops, they really need to address this. I usually have to work offline when I’m here

That being said, this would otherwise be my favorite coffee shop/lunch spot in the country. It’s one of the rare places that has both great food and coffee, and I’ve come here a lot for food. There’s also ample seating—I’ve never struggled to find a place to sit—in addition to being really well-decorated with a cool vibe. Their chicken sandwich and chicken biscuit are highlights.

I’m happy to amend this review straight to 5 stars if I hear that they’re getting their wifi situation fixed!

WiFi is down, which happens, but none of the staff have looked into it or even attempted to fix it. I went to the counter and before I could ask about it, the person working said a bit meanly “if you’re asking about the WiFi it’s very slow right now.” It wasn’t just slow. It was so slow that it wasn’t even allowing devices to connect—therefore it was down and generally would prompt looking into. The frustrating part is there was no way for me to know this without asking, and when I did ask the cashier seemed very annoyed and dismissive, and acted like I was being rude for asking. If you’re tired of people asking about it, maybe simply put up a sign over the WiFi sign saying that it’s slow/not working. For a cafe where many people come to work, it’s a huge inconvenience to order things, expecting to be able to work here, only to have to go somewhere else!
Nice coffee shop but the wifi often doesn’t work.

The new menu is definitely good!
I recommend the Piadinas.
Plenty of space to sit there and it’s quiet.
Bland food and slow service.

The people's market is one of my favorite places. Located across from Presbyterian, it is so convenient to stop in to grab lunch or coffee. Their staff is always so friendly and welcoming. The food is always on point. I love the salmon BLT, the smoked wings and the Cobb salad. The Green Latifah smoothie is delicious too!
Super fresh BUT Super expensive. The croissant was very big flaky buttery and delicious but I don't think it was worth the like $7...

reviews_data.review_text:
People's Market was not what I expected. Being a "market" I expected a lot of pre-made food and some fresh fruits & vegetables.
Food was made fresh when ordered and the restaurant had a lot of comfortable seating and a huge bar area with draft beer on tap plus wine and beer available for purchase to take home.  Free parking was available across the street and other lots had paid parking.  We were there early morning on a weekday so plenty of parking was available.  Great food, drinks & Staff at a great price.

I am gluten intolerant, but have a severe reaction so have to be celiac-like cautious. I unfortunately am glutened each time eating here despite getting the gluten free bread. It seems as though their precautions are not as strong as other places in CLT. Will still come for the coffee & atmosphere, just not the food.
A great place to chill out and have a coffee, would highly recommend !
Every time we come to Charlotte we visit here for breakfast. Their food is amazing! 🙌🏼

Ordered the salmon bowl for pickup and received this mess. It was sloppy, cold, and seemingly missing food. This photo was taken before even getting back in the car, so it was not due to traveling. Showed the manager this plate and she did nothing to rectify the situation, which tells me this poor product is typical at this establishment. Very poor quality, presentation, and disappointing plate to say the least. This was a terrible way to experience The People’s Market for the very first time. Will not be back. The fries (not pictured) were good though.
Testy and quick, recommend that place.
Friendly swift service and a delicious VEGAN breakfast burrito. I'd come back here for vegan breakfast 👌👌

Good service, good food at affordable prices, and they make DAMN GOOD coffee.
Also, they have vegan options!

Has potential but missed the mark. I got the smoked salmon flatbread which was paper thin, like a cracker. And as a smoked salmon lover, you are not supposed to put the salmon on anything hot or it will turn into baked cooked salmon! They clearly didn’t do this with the flatbread, so it looked like someone took a baked salmon filet and threw it on a pizza crust. Kind of ruined the texture and the taste and entire point of ordering a dish with smoked salmon.
Awesome place! Great coffee and vibes.

First time visiting  and was quit surprised of the atmosphere.  It was busy and a very diverse  crowd. Lots of vegan  options. My got the Salomon  BLT which said was ok but a bit greasy  for her liking.  But overall  I recommend  this business  bc it a healthy  place to eat.

I took a bite of my burger and I noticed it was pink inside. I immediately stopped eating. I already left the location so I tried to call but the phone kept ringing. I’m not sure how this can be made right when I can’t get in contact with anyone. I’d really just like my money back.

Order from this place regularly and it is delicious every single time. I've never been inside, so I can't speak for the actual place, but it's great for delivery.

They have sometimes been inconsistent with portions on their tomato soup - but it's delicious!
Excellent customer service! Food was amazing especially the baked chicken!! I will be back!
Amazing food, staff, and ambience! Will definitely be back❣️❣️❣️

This place is great! Bright, open market feel with lots of beers, wine and Coffees. Food is great, I had a prosciutto and fig pizza that looked so good I finished devouring it before I could even think to take a picture for Google. They have fresh baked goodies, made and baked right in the open market by a trained pastry chef. Smells of sweet caramelized baked goods and freshly brewed coffee from the moment you walk in the door. Gotta try this place!
Great place for delicious coffee and light snacks
Atmosphere and food 👍 5/5

I dig many aspects of this place and it's an attractive place. While there on 9.20.24 I wasn't thinking and curled my legs up with the tops of my feet touching the couch I was on. Bottoms of my feet weren't touching the fabric. (I had been wearing flips flops & I was fresh from the shower - I get no one could have known this but just so you know I hadn't slogged through dust and mud.) I also get this isn't what you do at a place of food. I had a good book; I was in another world. A person with blond curly hair stood a couple feet away and said 'this is a restaurant, you can't have your feet on furniture. You have to wear shoes.' She/They weren't wrong; I corrected myself immediately. But I was embarrassed in front of others. I'm no snowflake, but I did have a rough week. I'm autistic and my nervous system was raw. She couldn't have known any of this, nor is it her responsibility to take care of, but she could have been less public in her approach. She also didn't introduce that she worked there. Until I asked, I thought she was a patron who had been drinking at the bar; she had been sitting there for the first hour I was there. I first thought she was just another patron who maybe was over-stepping because alcohol. (To be clear I didn't give much heed to what drink or food was or wasn't in front of her. It's a bar so I just figured.)

This "complaint" isn't crazy deep, but be considerate when you have to correct someone. You're human, but so are the people who patronize your digs. ✌️
I will definitely be back the food was delicious. It’s a lot of space and kid friendly

The People's Market is hands down a hidden gem! My sister and I stopped by for breakfast before church, and we were absolutely blown away. Everything was fresh, flavorful, and you could taste the love in each bite. I ordered the Chicken Biscuit ($8.99) with Southern fried chicken and house-made pimiento cheese—pure perfection! My sister went for the Vegan Fried Chicken ($12.49) with fried oyster mushrooms, pickled cucumber, vegan slaw, and a bun, and she couldn't stop raving about how delicious and satisfying it was. If you're in the area, this place is a must-try! We'll definitely be back!

This place is definitely the best cafe I've been to. The food is incredible, as are the drinks. The prices are good. The staff is super nice and accommodating. It's always very clean and they have a nice variety of food depending on the time of day. There's definitely something for everyone. CPCC really has the best location of any school in Charlotte. This place is in walking distance.

i'm not one to write bad reviews for a local place and would come here at least once a week, but after a run-in with the manager (or shift manager?) earlier this afternoon where we never received our food, I won't be returning again. The woman was extremely rude to my friend who never received a deli item she ordered and treated us like we were stupid the entire time we were trying to explain what the situation was, and gave off the impression that she thought we were lying or trying to scam them out of money. She refused to acknowledge our proof of the purchase going through through apple pay along with the text we were sent that the food was ready for pickup, and hardly made an effort to find the order on the P.O.S system while doubling down that there's simply no way the order was mistakenly put under a different name as I suggested. After a much too long back-and-forth with her very clearly not being interested in helping us figure out what had happened, she storms off pissed saying "whatever i'll give you your refund," finally asks for our number to look up to find the order (why couldn't she have just done that from the start???), and sees that we were right and that it was under a very different name.

There was absolutely 0 reason to treat your customers like they're stupid – she approached the situation from the start very agitated like we were guilty of something and was being very disrespectful with how she spoke to us. I have worked customer service for years and I cant imagine interacting with guests like that who had approached being polite and just wanted their problem fixed. I was looking forward to showing my friend this spot, but the entire experience left us both feeling weird.
The Lavendar Vanilla Latte is the best latte I've ever had! Friendly staff, quick service and chill atmosphere
Yummy food, good vibes! Haven't tried the coffee yet but I'll be back to remedy that soon.
This cafe is a beautiful cafe near uptown, Charlotte. The pizza is especially the bomb. Highly reccomend.

I ordered through DoorDash for 13 food items. There was no option to include additional instruction. So I literally made a phone call to let them know to write the food name on the box label. When I arrived, it was ready and none of the label was written. I asked the guy to write it, and he was super mad and upset. Then he went and wrote it for me. I reached home and not a single side was included such as potato chips and other sides that was all selected. Not only that couple of items were missing as well. Fruit juice and ice tea was a separate order, which was not in the package. I will not recommend this for Doordash order. Included pics and videos of indoor and also the guy who was upset.

The People’s Market offers a warm, inviting atmosphere paired with a nice selection of food and drinks. It’s a great place for a casual breakfast or lunch and convenient for pickup orders. It’s also a go-to spot to work remote.

Great atmosphere for a bit and some casual drink. Got the chicken sandwich and side salad. Salad was great with homemade ranch and the chicken sandwich one of the best I’ve had in Charlotte. Would highly recommend checking this place out!

I was on my way to church and my wife needed some sustenance ASAP! The Peoples Market has some of the freshest smoothies in CLT so we forced a stop.  My ordered her smoothie and a ham and cheese croissant and it was everything she needed.

You can taste the quality of the ingredients.  I called to place an order over the phone, and they don't take phone orders, but they had the smoothie ready as soon as we got there.

The servers were friendly and personable, I will definitely be back.
I have been here only for coffee, but it has been delicious each time.

Love this spot, my go to for coffee, breakfast and lunch!! Such a vibe, food is amazing (market bagel and salmon blt are my faves), owner and staff are great plus parking!! a lovely place to post up and work remotely too 💛 thanks for all you guys do!
Fantastic space. A benefit to the community as well.

It was my first time at the People's Market. This unique market is steps away from Novant/Presbyterian Main and CPCC's main campus. loved the whole vibe here. Reminded me of my college days. Great spot to catch up with friends over breakfast or lunch. Nice healthy menu! Fun atmosphere and a nice variety of wines and beers!
I had the tasty soft breakfast tacos and a delicious mint tea. Hubby had a breakfast Burrito that did not disappoint along with his coffee. Our daughter had toast, eggs and  bacon, and a nice warm tea!  We will make this one of our "go-to spots" on our list where to take family and friends when they come to visit us in the Queen City!
Delicious vegan breakfast burrito.
Love the vibes here. Great place to grad some coffee and work
Excellent Vegan donuts!
We have a monthly meeting here. Great atmosphere and food.
Loved everything I got - chicken avocado wrap, sweet potato fries, honey bee latte, and a croissant! Cute atmosphere with lots of seating.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Fries, Sweet Potato Fries, Chicken Avocado Wrap

reviews_data.review_text:
I discovered this special café one day after a doctor’s appointment. The entire Elizabeth neighborhood is very cool with lots of restaurants and bars as well as trolley service that runs throughout.

I had the ham and cheese croissant and it was excellent! Whatever cheese they use in that thing is special. I also had a peach blossom iced tea with elderberry syrup and I was tempted to get a second.

The bakery is on the left. The bar is in the center, and the order and pick up window for savory foods is on the right. You can order food while sitting at the bar as well.

I really enjoyed the openness of the space as well as all the natural light. The garage doors are probably fun to open in the spring and fall. Since they have a kids menu, I’m excited to bring my whole family back to enjoy it!
One of my favorite coffee shops to get a bite and some excellent coffee.
Breakfast burrito was yummy.

Freaking looooveeeee this place for lunch! Whenever I work in Uptown I’ve just gotta come here to get their chicken avocado wrap - DELICIOUS EVERY TIME!!!! Vibe is so upbeat and modern, food is made quickly, and it’s just a grand ol’ time all around. Highly recommend!
A great place to work and have coffee/tea. Baristas are lovely and the food selection is great for a morning work session.

This is set up cafeteria style. You find a table and then go order your food/drinks. There are three food counters. Great variety, for breakfast and lunch. Very clean and plenty of seating. There's also a private room you can rent for meetings. Food is priced great and tastes so good. I had the smash burger and salad. My friend had a BLT. Definitely recommend!
Great prices on breakfast and coffee. If I lived closer, I'd be here every day.
Amazing vibe with good food and coffee.

My go to’s are the iced Vanilla Lavender latte (Homemade syrups) and any of the danishes, but Pastries are always delicious and nice to see them being made in the bakery area while hanging around. It draws a diverse crowd so always an interesting atmosphere.
The cinnamon roll croissants have me in a chock hold.😃🤦🏾‍♀️🥰🥰🥰😍

reviews_data.review_text: The People's Market is such a clutch spot for good coffee, good food and good vibes. I'm a regular here, so I've tried a lot of things on the menu and I've never been disappointed. This is also a good spot for remote workers. I've worked from People's Market several times and have always been able to find a parking spot, a comfy seat and a power outlet.

A great spot to read, get some work done, or meet up with friends. There’s a lot of space and a wide range of seating options suitable for groups small and large. The food is delicious (though a little pricey) and the coffee/pastries are delicious. It’s a vibrant atmosphere with kind and attentive staff—highly recommend!
Great place to hangout for writing, reading, meeting friends or colleauges or just a coffee - Excellent Lattes.

reviews_data.review_text: Sweet potatoes are good ! Fried oyster sandwich was decent, I do think the sandwich was overpriced. As far as the atmosphere it was really clean , but it was FREEZING inside!
A lovely spot in the heart of Elizabeth. The brekkie burrito slaps and the vibe is top tier. Do it.
Delicious food & great service.
Is ok. It is very loud and hard to find seating. The sandwich is small for the price but tasty.
Gluten free maple muffin is delicious.  The croissants are way too dry. Coffee is delicious and staff is amazing.  Avoid cheese danish. Mine was not edible.
Extremely quick service, friendly staff, delicious food and drinks - added to my list of favorite spots! The burger in particular was incredible. Make sure to ask for extra house sauce!!
Don’t try to order catering on the website. Management won’t get the request and the options are not congruent with what they say they offer.

I was in Charlotte and wanted a place to work where I could grab something to eat and some good coffee.

The setup for ordering and getting your food was a bit different but the cashier explained it when my order was complete.

The menu for breakfast was pretty good and definitely a step above a regular coffee shop.

The only downside was that the coffee only came on one size. And it wasn’t very big. But was reasonably priced.

The atmosphere was a mix of people meeting up and working like me. I was able to work until my computer battery got low. I didn’t see an outlet so I packed up and went to another coffee shop. But that was really my only gripe. Not worth knocking a star though cause I probably needed to move and make room for others anyway. 🤪
Great vibes. Didn’t have to turn on headphones to drown out bad music. Perfect  space for WFH folks that want to step out. Can’t beat the free parking too

i came in on an afternoon and this tall guy was "helping" me pick out a coffee, and it was a terrible iced latte, the espresso was watery and my drink had no body, there are so many better places for food and coffee in the area. will not be returning.
The perfect welcome to Elizabeth spot! A open space for working and or connecting with loved ones. Truly one of my all time faves in Elizabeth.

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing Food and Atmosphere! Love this place although only been once LOL 😆. They got me hooked already! I definitely suggest the Vegan Chicken Sandwich. My Wife said it was the Best she ever had!!! I enjoyed the pastries they had as well. Had a Sea Salt Chocolate Chip Cookie that was Amazing!! Should have gotten more than one when I was there. GO TO THIS PLACE! 🖤

reviews_data.review_text: Great neighborhood spot. I like that they are open for all meals and have lots of healthy and fun options

As a vegan, The People’s Market has been a favorite of mine since they were on East. But now since going gluten-free also,  they are my top choice. It's perfect for a quick breakfast, meeting up with friends, or grabbing a coffee while working from home. I'm grateful for their hearty, fulfilling breakfast options and delicious baked treats. I do not take it for granted. Please don’t ever leave me.

Went here on our way out of town for lunch. I eat plant based and went with a gluten free friend and another with no dietary restrictions, so we wanted to try to find somewhere we could all eat.
I had the vegan breakfast burrito which was so good! One friend got a chicken caesar wrap (yay, gluten free wrap!) and the other got a reuben.
We also grabbed some lattes at the coffee counter which were awesome! I had an iced oat milk latte with vanilla and it was perfectly creamy, nutty, and sweet.
This seems like a really nice place to stop in for a bite, a coffee, a snack, or even a bottle of wine to take home. They also have a bar in the middle which seemed to have beer on draft. I also saw plenty of people there to work on laptops and collaborate with others (there is a conference room possibly able to be rented?) so it would be an awesome place to get work done, hang with friends, or grab something to go.
There is also parking for Elizabeth St. shops just across the street!

reviews_data.review_text: Loved it! Was stopping by and was pleasantly surprised. Got a cappuccino with lavender vanilla syrup and an everything danish! Coffee wasn’t too sweet and was made quickly and orderly, and the danish is soooo yummy and flakey. The lovely woman, Leika, at the counter offered to heat it up for me even though they were busy, so I’m very happy 🤍🤍

We stopped by for brunch. It was obviously more for people conducting business, but I still enjoyed visiting. The food was very good, but not really like anything you'd find elsewhere so my very young daughter who is picky wasnt really a fan (she didnt like the smoky syrup like sauce on her oatmeal and berries or the flavors of my bagel). Still, they had free water, beautiful lattes, and large portions. It was busy, but not uncomfortable.

So, I walk in on for a bite to eat on a bright Sunday. This place has been haunting me in Google Maps for several days. I tend to avoid uptown because of parking, but this place was well worth it. I parked on the side street but later saw a parking lot across the street.

I sat at the bar because it was the first thing I really noticed when I walked in. It was mildly busy that day. There were so many smiling faces, and the staff immediately assisted me when I stated it was my first time in.

I ordered the vegan platter (yes, of course, I want the sausage with it) and a lavender vanilla latte with oat milk.

Later, before leaving, I went to the bakery, which is located right inside and to the left and got the donut (vanilla birthday cake) and muffin (chocolate chip). The vegan and gluten-free were on the top shelf and clearly labeled in the case #win

Back to the meal... I ordered and paid at the bar and was told to wait for the text that I would receive when my order was ready. I was directed to the back of the store for the food and the bakery for the coffee, but the bartender grabbed and delivered the items directly to me (so many thanks!)

The food automatically came in to go containers. I appreciated that because it made it easier for me to go from the bar to a table to work (no laptops were allowed at the bar 10a-2p.

I completely enjoyed everything I ate! It was flavored and cooked to perfection 👌🏾

To say I'll be going back there is an understatement! You'll have to try this place! There are plenty of vegan options, and the price was VERY good for brunch!

Not a full 5 stars because I asked for iced water, and the staff at the bakery counter told me to get the water from the community container. It's awesome that they offer this, but there was no ice.
Also, they had me pay on a device and left the device in front of me for most of my meal. It was awkward and made me feel like I was supposed to do something more.
Great breakfast and lovely service.
Good smash burger
I frequent The People's Market for the food, price, and atmosphere. It has become my go place.

Got all the way home to find the substitute I asked for was not put not on my v bkfast wrap. Tried to call …& got an answer on an understandably busy Saturday from Meredith who was so kind as to void the transaction & offer a comp item upon my return. Thank you queen! I’ll be going back asap for something yummy forsure.
Solid matcha, and the chicken bacon wrap was awesome. Nice lunch option, and I loved that there was space to work/hang. Would love to see some seasonal drink specials though!
Neat place, people were friendly and the burger was juicy and tasty
The baked goods were phenomenal and so was that smash burger. Very chill and peaceful atmosphere. I will definitely be returning.

I had the fried vegan chicken sandwich and it was horrible it was chewy not crispy at all I also had Irish cream coffee which tastes like water down hot chocolate maybe they have something else on the menu that's better but for me to spend 20dollars for those two items and neither one of them was good was a waste of money!!
The baristas are so rude and they do not know how to make anything right! The lattes were so watery…. The egg in the market bagel was also undercooked… will not be returning

The place is nice, the bathrooms are very clean I do have to say. I am very shocked as here in Jersey, that would not be a thing. The customer service is 10/10, the human that made my chai latte really has a craft for making latte art. Also, second best chai latte I’ve ever had. I cannot really rate the food as I only had an almond croissant, but even the at was very tasty. I will certainly go again! 10/10 I recommend.
Fun place. Great sandwiches. Lots of drink and eat choices. Pizza looked good. I will definitely return.
Chicken wrap was the best ever!!

I used to go to People’s Market at its old location and was excited to learn it reopened. Unfortunately that excitement was short lived after I got my breakfast. I ordered a chicken biscuit and the biscuit was inedible. It was dry and fell apart when I cut into it. I have never had dark meat on a biscuit before either and it had a lot of fat.

The sunny side was the chai tea latte.

I went to have brunch with friends today. I went to the bathroom to find out there was no soap in the restroom, only hand sanitizer. I notified a worker and she said “she was aware and they had no soap only sanitizer in the bathroom”. I should have left but I decided to stay and get my order. I am now having a horrible upset  stomach and haven’t been able to eat anything since my visit. This unfortunately was my first time visiting the restaurant and maybe my last. I didn’t even think about the sanitation of the workers handling the food! Hand sanitizer is NOT soap and does not wash the germs away! I’m disappointed, disgusted, and now sick.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Sorry to hear about your People’s Market experience. Let me be the first to say that we take food safety and customer service very seriously. We have achieved and maintained an 99.5 sanitation score for several months. With regards to employee not helping you when the dispenser was out, we would like to learn who you spoke to in order to provide more training. If you don’t mind, can you contact the store and leave your contact information. We would like to fix your experience as much as possible. 

Cory 
Owner & Founder

reviews_data.review_text: Came for a meeting and got a traditional Iced Coffee with SF Carmel and cream. It was deliciously decadent and smooth. I also got a Sausage Breakfast Burrito with Verde and loved every bite. It was delicious. Ambiance is nice too.
The best place! Great chill but welcoming atmoshphere. The hands-down best Smashburger in town. A great salad (the Hipster is sublime). Great bartenders.
Our first time here, we came for a cocktail class and grabbed some lunch. They were super busy, but service and food was great. We will definitely be back to try other dishes.

I know takeout is a gamble but my entire breakfast bowl is horrible... especially the barely cooked turkey bacon

. Barely toasted English muffin
. almost melted cheese
No effort whatsoever

Great meeting spot to come just chill with a few friends. They also have a private conference room that can be reserved. They have a wide variety of things from pastries to alcohol. This place comes highly recommended.
Great casual place to grab a quick bite or no drink.
The food was great .and the service was great. Will comeback
Some of the best coffee in Charlotte and the food is good too!
A fantastic cafe, great environment, awesome gluten free foods & desserts

I want to start by saying that the coffee staff is amazing and very friendly. They get my drink right every time. With that being sad, the food leaves something to be desired. I get a Market bagel every now and then and for the most part it's usually good. Today however was a very disappointing experience. I spend a lot of money here weekly to be playing roulette with the food hoping that whoever is back there cares enough to put my food together. My market bagel was not toasted, the bacon was not the siracha bacon, the avocado looked like it was just thrown on there and the egg was just plain sad. I come here for the coffee, the staff and pastries. The food needs some work.
Food & drinks were great

reviews_data.review_text: The hidden gem of Elizabeth nestled in a serene location is a perfect weekend workspace. With a tranquil ambiance, it provides a peaceful environment to work, accompanied by exceptional coffee and a well-stocked bar for those seeking a delightful break. A unique spot that combines productivity with relaxation.

reviews_data.review_text: The ambience was super amicable and loved the biscuits and the burrito. Location is accessible being very close to the uptown. Staff was very friendly and the market has a very cool vibe to it. With couches and other seating areas, its like a place for all or anytime of the day. Can’t wait to be back and try other options on the menu.
Great food, staff is fine, plenty of room to work remotely without feeling like your stealing space from folks
Great Single patty burger! Ordered ahead and prompt service !
I got the smash burger Jo got the salmon blt.  We were impressed with our food, the local beer selection and the local spirits used in cocktails. Will definitely come back!

This review is overdue. I used Uber Eats for brunch on Sunday, 01-15-23. I ordered the CJ's country boy bowl, creamy grits, mixed fruit, a large jasmine tea, and a regular apple chai-der.

This review is reminding me that I need to stop by to dine in. The bowl was filling by itself. The grits were on point; the food was still hot when delivered. The fruit was fresh. The drinks were hot, too. The jasmine was good, but I could use another apple chai on a cold day like today. I'd only had regular chai up to that point and wanted to try something different. It was very good.

The good reviews helped me decide to try them that day. Hopefully this one will help you decide, too.

Plenty of vegan options. Food was delicious.
Coffee was good.
Ambience was very good. Friendly and helpful staff.

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent customer service and food.  Very clean and well maintained.  Wonderful atmosphere, laid back and spacious.

My partner and I came here for lunch and ordered a regular pizza, but asked to make it vegan. The staff person who took our order was very kind and let us know that it would not be a problem which was perfect for me because I am lactose intolerant and have been vegan for 2 years. The pizza came out quickly and it was delicious. Unfortunately, we didn't realize it until we were done eating that the cook in the back put real parmesan cheese on top of the vegan cheese 😭. We saw little white specks on the pizza as we were eating, but we also asked for the balsamic vinaigrette (which we know is vegan) and it has little specks in it so we thought it was that. However, after we completely devoured the pizza we saw dry white specks in the box that were definitely parmesan. I brought it up to John, one of the workers, and he was very responsive, apologetic, and offered to refund us for the pizza. I was okay with that and not super upset because I thought it was just a light sprinkle of cheese but shortly after we left People's Market at 6pm, I got the worst nausea, and I stayed up until 3am with terribleee stomach pain and a lot of mucus buildup. I have never felt that much stomach pain in my life. Apparently, there was way more cheese than we realized.

I love the People's Market so I would go back again but I'm a little scarred and will definitely double check with the order taker to make sure that any non-vegan items are specified to be left out on the ticket.

TLDR: Ordered a vegan pizza and the cook put real cheese on it. Tip for customers - make sure the order ticket specifies to leave non-vegan items off of the food item to be sure.

Great place for coffee and pastries. The coffee is really good, and they bake their own pastries on site, and they are excellent. My favorite is the cinnamon roll croissant. On this occasion, I had the pumpkin waffle with brie whipped cream and candied pecans, which was outstanding. So delicious, it was worth the calories spent. It's seasonal, so get it before it's gone.

The Peoples Market in Elizabeth, Charlotte, NC offers some truly tasty breakfast options—my bagel was great and the grits were absolutely amazing, rich and flavorful. The coffee was solid as well, a nice complement to the meal. The atmosphere is cozy and inviting, making it a pleasant spot to start the day. They also have some good looking desserts. We got the Oreo brownie and it was pretty good, but will try something else next time.

They also had a THC infused pizza for $23.99, which I have never seen before… At first I just saw a frozen pizza for $23.99 and couldn’t believe it was so expensive, until I realized what it was.
Usually a really good spot to work but the air is ALWAYS broken!

We need this kind of option in Ballantyne! How quaint! Coffee, tea, and pastries at one counter. Draft beer in the center. Prepared food in the fridge! Huge organic drink selection. Warm sandwiches, cold sandwiches, and a large variety of chips...and seating galore! I love this atmosphere. I plan to go back! Soon!

So a little bit of code to decipher, didnt see any signage that helped....
It wasn't crowded when we arrived, but if got more crowded while there.   It's a hard space, so noise was a factor.

We will visit again..., hopefully we can figure out where to order what....

I would not consider this an allergy-friendly restaurant. Quite frankly, if a kitchen and restaurant do not care about the health of their customers, what are they even doing cooking food for other people?

I ordered the chicken avocado wrap with a gluten-free tortilla (which I paid extra for) and asked for no cheese. I also ordered a grilled cheese with fries and ketchup. I was a little taken aback when I realized my wrap wasn’t labeled gluten-free, but I tried to keep an open mind. Then I noticed it had cheese in it as well.

I called the restaurant to confirm whether it was a gluten-free wrap. The person on the phone just tried to describe it to me, but honestly, there was no way to tell. I was left with food that I couldn’t be sure was safe for me to eat.

The grilled cheese we ordered was burned, but I didn’t even bother bringing it up because it was already clear they had no process for handling issues with orders and didn’t consider it important enough to escalate to a manager. I did mention that they forgot the ketchup; however, the woman on the phone decided to blame the Grubhub driver for that.

Explain to me how it’s the driver’s job to pick up ketchup, napkins, and silverware. They work for Grubhub—they’re a delivery driver. Why should they be doing the restaurant’s job? Plus, the bag was stapled shut when it arrived. Was he supposed to bring those items in his pockets?

Really disappointed in how highly reviewed this place is because it does not deserve it and I had a terrible breakfast because of it. Firstly I’m not sure why they don’t have a single basic smoothie on the menu, but I decided to order the one with cinnamon because I thought between that and chia seeds, it would be a less intense addition to the smoothie. It was not, there was so much cinnamon and protein powder that it was unbearable to drink. Secondly, I would like to know why restaurants don’t seem to be seasoning their food anymore. The barbacoa breakfast tacos I received were nearly inedible. There was way too much meat, they barely put any cheese or egg on it and it tasted like they didn’t even salt the meat. The prices are decent but that’s about the only good thing I have to say about my meal.

Ordered their “popular” market bagel. If you are going to make egg selection an option, they need to 1. Learn how to cook a medium egg and 2. Don't serve undercooked eggs. with basically raw egg white. You threw a quarter of an avocado on the sandwich, not even sliced. Listen if you’re tired of making breakfast just stop because you destroyed mine. The other sides and my partners breakfast is “mid” at best. Thanks for wasting my money on your garbage breakfast. I would just close up if you cannot even make an egg to an order.

Really enjoyed dinner at The People's Market. My wife and I thought the smashburger was awesome. It doesnt look imposing, but it tasted amazing! The mushroom pizza was pretty good. I prefer it cooked a little more, but it was still delicious. My wife's salad was solid as well. After a beer at the bar, we finished with the malted iced coffee which was a perfect closer! Service was quick and the staff was friendly. We'll definitely be back.
Burnt!!! I believe in first impressions…..
Excellent service specifically the coffee shop!
Excellent service and breakfast was amazing. Atmosphere is always welcoming 🌞

I was driving around and stumbled upon this place. I love the whole concept of this restaurant! the atmosphere, the service and especially the food. I had a gingerbread chai latte which was very much delicious and their fried chicken sandwich definitely will be back!

Food and coffee was so good. Love the vibe. Wish the WiFi worked though. I came to do homework and was unable to get connected so I  had to leave. Once that issue is resolved, this place will be 10/10!

I came to grab a grubhub order and I planned to order for myself as well; this was at 2:00pm on 1/7/25. I never made an order because of how unwelcoming and unpleasant the cashier was being all because I asked where to pick up the online orders. She gave me attitude and pointed to the back of the store with a menacing look on her face...there are no signs in the front of the store indicating to driver's to go to the back of the store to pick up orders. With that, I didn't want to invite that horrible energy into my life again so I didn't make my order and I canceled the grubhub pick up SMH l. I thought I found my next spot to get tea, guess not.

I meant to write this sooner but the tall brown skinned gentleman (Jameel I believe), his customer service was awesome. It was my first time and he was professional, funny, and made the Lavendar iced matcha great! I also tried the sweet potatoe pecan loaf WOW! It was the perfect size as well, not too small or big.
Anyway again great service and even though I took the items to go, the inside was very big.
Picked up my food, and employee told me that my name is weird. Really classy!

This place is relaxed, service is good and people are friendly/pretty chill.

Everyday food with a little flair and creativity, locally owned, and more Vegan/Vegetarian options and substitutions than more places. Very accommodating since my last visit.

Vegan Philly (V) - Overall, it's good. It's just impossible beef with condiments - exactly as described, which I appreciate. It does need a little more "pizzazz" like seasoning (herbs & spices are vegan - idk why restaurants are afraid to use them) , lettuce, tomatoes... Etc. However, I must admit that I prefer it slightly more than the Beyond Steak. Nevertheless, my previous comment still stands and I highly recommend they make this more like a "chopped cheese" since its Impossible Burger with the chunks not being so big  but can still call it a Philly since it's just chopped meat anyway.

Vegan Fried Chicken (V) - It's GOOD AND SEASONED (I need to know their secrets lol) and the flavors work well together. The only problem is the oyster mushroom stem. They fry the entire thing but the stem is too rough and inedible. I wish they would cut it off. I've cooked these mushrooms before and you can cut most of it off leaving the rest intact.

I really do like this place, and they do a good job but I think some minor adjustments could make certain menu items much better.
Just another "market" where you herd in and herd out....nothing special.
It truly is a great hangout spot. Definitely worth recommending for a casual get together.
Very expensive mid food.

It had been a while since my last visit to people's market.  Went there the other day, and the vibe inside is VERY nice.

The staff were informative and helpful.   They seemed welcoming and especially accommodating when dealing with my 4 year old son.  Who, at the time, was intent on dismantling their Christmas tree.

The selection of baked goods was phenomenal.  My lil guy was thrilled with the Chocolate donut, covered in icing and sprinkles.

I went back a couple of days later and had a smashburger from the grill. It was delicious.

I will admit, the sandwich did not come as ordered... (keep in mind my toddler was staging considerable distractions) I asked for a "Bacon BBQ burger"without pickled onions, and ended up with a "People's smash burger" which had a hefty load of pickles on it...

Even with that easily understandable error, the burger was pretty great.  I have to imagine the other sandwich would've been even more enjoyable.

We'll be back soon

Wonder surroundings with a good mix of food and drink offerings. The meeting room is it over the top.

Ordered from here 3 times through Ubereats. The grits are amazing but any other food I get always has something wrong with it. The waffle was half-raw and the fruits are always close to rotting (not fresh at all).
We go every time my wife has to go in for treatments. She especially loves the pastries.

Fried chicken was great, and the gravy was super tasty! Grits were very good. Sausage was very smokey, so mame sure that is your thing. Everything was good, but is all served in a to-go container. Coffee and smoothie bars are cool, but coffee bar was out of all seasonal syrups advertised on the door and bar. And smoothies are a bit pricey at $10-15/each.

I ordered a pickup order and they forgot my hashbrowns for my kid's burrito side as well as the honey mustard sauce for my kid's chicken tender. They can't even get an order correct... I tried to call them and no answer..... The oreo brownie was incredibly dry and old.... Horrible. Never returning

I’ve been to many spots to try a good chocolate croissant and I can say this spot has the best one 🔥 it’s Sooooo good. This spot it’s a vibe too!

Update- 12/7 second time coming and the WiFi is not working. That sucks for me because I plan to get work done and I end up having to go elsewhere. Please get this fixed!!!
Best burger in Charlotte.

I got the vegan breakfast burrito (with the vegan sausage but without the vegan cheese) plus an oat milk mocha and an oreo brownie. Everything was so yummy. The spicy green sauce that comes with the burrito is awesome. Very spicy.

I would have called and taken this up with the store personally but they do not have a phone number and do not allow calls so unfortunately my only way to make them aware of the serious food hazard I just experienced when trying to eat my food I ordered from them via Door Dash is to make this review and post it so that as many people as possible will know and can keep themselves safe.

This could have been disastrous.

Thank you, Leigh.
I had the black bean burger and it was very delicious!
Thanksgiving meal def hit the spot.

Went in for something quick to hold me over until a late afternoon lunch. Shared a Peoples Smashburger and a bag of chips with my mom - we loved it. I really enjoyed the atmosphere as well. It seems like a good spot to work and catch up with friends. And they have a bit of everything including infused drinks in the cooler 😉.

I love this place, but the wifi is really inconsistent. For somewhere with a dedicated conference room and lots of folks clearly working on their laptops, they really need to address this. I usually have to work offline when I’m here

That being said, this would otherwise be my favorite coffee shop/lunch spot in the country. It’s one of the rare places that has both great food and coffee, and I’ve come here a lot for food. There’s also ample seating—I’ve never struggled to find a place to sit—in addition to being really well-decorated with a cool vibe. Their chicken sandwich and chicken biscuit are highlights.

I’m happy to amend this review straight to 5 stars if I hear that they’re getting their wifi situation fixed!

WiFi is down, which happens, but none of the staff have looked into it or even attempted to fix it. I went to the counter and before I could ask about it, the person working said a bit meanly “if you’re asking about the WiFi it’s very slow right now.” It wasn’t just slow. It was so slow that it wasn’t even allowing devices to connect—therefore it was down and generally would prompt looking into. The frustrating part is there was no way for me to know this without asking, and when I did ask the cashier seemed very annoyed and dismissive, and acted like I was being rude for asking. If you’re tired of people asking about it, maybe simply put up a sign over the WiFi sign saying that it’s slow/not working. For a cafe where many people come to work, it’s a huge inconvenience to order things, expecting to be able to work here, only to have to go somewhere else!
Nice coffee shop but the wifi often doesn’t work.

The new menu is definitely good!
I recommend the Piadinas.
Plenty of space to sit there and it’s quiet.
Bland food and slow service.

The people's market is one of my favorite places. Located across from Presbyterian, it is so convenient to stop in to grab lunch or coffee. Their staff is always so friendly and welcoming. The food is always on point. I love the salmon BLT, the smoked wings and the Cobb salad. The Green Latifah smoothie is delicious too!
Super fresh BUT Super expensive. The croissant was very big flaky buttery and delicious but I don't think it was worth the like $7...
